    "claim": "The `isSolvent` modifier performs its post-state LTV check against `exchangeRateInfo.exchangeRate`, but both `leveragedPosition()` and `repayWithCollateral()` refresh that price before calling an external swapper and never refresh it again afterward. If the oracle can be moved during the swap path, the position is validated against a stale pre-swap rate instead of the worse post-swap rate.",
    "impact": "A borrower can finish the transaction undercollateralized while still passing the contract's solvency check, creating bad debt that is only discovered later and can be pushed onto liquidations/insurance.",
    "paths": [
      "Use `repayWithCollateral()` with a whitelisted swapper that sells collateral through the oracle market (or otherwise worsens the oracle during the swap). The pair checks solvency with the pre-swap exchange rate even though the remaining collateral is worth less at the end of the transaction.",
      "Open a leveraged position through a whitelisted swapper that can worsen the oracle after `_updateExchangeRate()` runs but before the modifier's final check, so the new debt is accepted against an outdated, more favorable rate."
    ]
  },
